2.1.4 Declaring variables to store data
	- You can omit the type delcarations
		ex)
			============================================================
			// Instead of 
			// val question: String = "How are you?"
			val question = "How are you?" 

			// Instead of
			// val answer: Int = 42
			val answer = 42
			============================================================

	* If you use a floating-point constant, the variable will have the type "Double"
		ex)
			============================================================
			val yearsToCompute = 7.5e6
			============================================================


	- If you try to assign a variable later, you won't be able to infer the type for the variable
		-> you need to specify the type explictly
			ex)
				============================================================
				fun main(){
					// specify the type explicitly
					val answer: Int

					answer = 42
				}
				============================================================